phrases: Tamaki Mari-san and Kobuchizawa Shirase-san will be embarking
on a trip to Antarctica next month.
It is still a little hard to believe this is happening,
but I will do my best where I am going!
You should not have waited so long.
I felt like I had become a big sister.
We can play together tomorrow, too.
This is the new Antarctic Icebreaker ship,
Its basic performance has not changed,
but there have been some internal modifications,
and as you can see, it is had a big external makeover!
But the truth is, we will not get to board it until we reach Australia.
So, let us make the jump to Australia right now!
You do not have to make fun of me.
By comparison, our next report's not until we reach Australia,
but look at her freaking out already.
What am I going to do?!
They can work it out in editing.
For now, just do your vocal warm-ups.
Have you been doing your warm-ups?
She sells seashells on the sea floor.
Not quite right, but close enough.
Why would a person sell seashells?
Please do not try to dissect it.
She spoke just fine at morning assembly...
Because there is no one she sees as an enemy here.
When someone she is hostile to is around, it is like
You are talking about me, are not you?
We are really getting on this thing, huh?
There is a lot to think about, is not there?
Including our body weight, we are allowed 100 kilograms all together.
It should be more than enough.
Yeah, but we are staying for three months, right?
That is over 90 changes of clothes!
Although it is a journey, once we arrive, we will just be living life like normal.
And there will be lots of work to do, so they say it will pass quickly...
But when you start thinking and packing things into the boxes,
it does end up being quite a lot...
Hey, have you not even gotten started?
But it just needs to be less than 100 kilograms, including body weight, right?
I can take upwards of 58 kilograms of luggage!
Underestimating your weight is a serious crime.
Please leave my arm flab alone...
This might be harder than I thought...
Mari-chan, how many times do I have to tell you to carry up your own laundry?
I do not think you will need cooking supplies.
I bought them all just for this trip!
You will be with tons of people who can speak foreign languages!
That should do it, I think.
You should consult with Shirase-san, too.
There might be some specific things you will need.
But do you really think this will be enough?
I will be gone for over three months.
Sis... are you sure you can handle this?
It is not like that pamphlets tell us what to bring...
Because it is an adult thing.
The one I thought I would lost!
Wow, I would totally forgotten about that.
You do not actually have to test it, you know.
But I have not seen it in so long!
After three years, it might not even work.
You sure loved this thing, huh?
After all, it is the only game I ever beat you at.
You could not beat me at all,
so you said you would lend it to me as long as I wanted it.
But I did beat it before then!
So, how did things go in Tokyo?
Pretty well, for the most part.
Did Antarctica manage to get through her report?
Shirase-chan does not have to report for a while yet.
She swings between super-confident and super-timid.
I was talking to Hinata-chan about that...
Is that the girl from your job?
But Yuzuki-chan did the report perfectly, so...
Is that the girl from Hokkaido?
Well, do not push yourself too hard.
If you fail, you will just regret it all the more.
A Place Further Than the Universe Kobuchizawa Takako
I am not sure it will fit...
I will send you pictures of warm things.
Does your snot freeze in Antarctica?
I want to have some shaved ice.
Is it true there is a UFO buried in the ice there?
Feels like I am changing schools or something, huh?
I will not be seeing you for a while...
What kind of reception did you expect?
I just did not think they would make such a big deal over it!
When Shirase-chan said she was going to Antarctica,
everyone just made fun of her.
Because they did not think she would make it, I guess.
Besides, some people still make fun of her.
I will not be able to come here for three months, either.
I just was not sure how I would feel...
You know, maybe it is best not to show off so much.
A lot of people think you are getting full of yourself.
I am not showing off anything.
It is just, they are saying some awful things about you.
That you shoplifted from convenience stores to raise money.
That you were messing around with boys in Kabukicho and stuff.
I am telling you, people think you are full of yourself.
Are you sure you should just leave with this unresolved?
Once you are back, it is only going to get worse...
Would this be Megu-chan, by chance?
That is right, you guys have not met yet...
I am Miyake Hinata, Kimari's co-worker!
I do not know, I just heard it...
I will search out the culprit!
Remember, we are heading out tomorrow.
I cannot just sit back while someone spreads those ridiculous rumors!
Starting a fight now will not help anybody.
You have ignored all the nasty rumors so far, right?
This is not the same thing!
To claim we have been messing around with boys in Shinjuku...
We did go to Shinjuku, though.
But we were not messing around!
Do not fight mean with mean.
Besides, you are not alone right now.
I mean you have people to vent with!
This must be what it feels to grab a drink on the way back from work.
Okay, let us have one more!
It is payday, so the old man'll cover it.
You sure hate to let things go, do not you?
Well, the people spreading the rumors are the ones in the wrong.
Why should I yield to them?
I just want to scream at the top of my lungs!
Then let us go to karaoke!
If we do it within the hour, we are probably good.
I have never been to karaoke.
How can you all do something so embarrassing?
It is okay to get it all out.
I am so glad I was not there.
I never thought I would get to do this stuff the night before I left.
I mean, I have not gotten to hang out with you much
since I decided to go to Antarctica.
Though I guess that was a relief to you...
But it was not like that for me at all.
I have been thinking this whole time...
About how I want to go far away,
about how I hate being where I am,
I never knew why I felt that way.
It was probably because of you, Megu-chan.
I am always uncertain, needing you to fuss over me.
Always clinging to you, asking what I should do...
Yeah, and I always hated that.
I think I wanted to change it.
So I would not just be clinging to you; I would not be worthless.
I would be someone you could play video games with.
So I am going to do my best out there.
Make sure you get breakfast in Tokyo, okay?
Why did not you wake me up?
Sorry to bother you right before you set out.
I am saying, we are not friends anymore.
You still have not realized it?
Where do you think the rumor about you and Antarctica going to Shinjuku came from?
Did you tell anyone about it?
The first time you met Antarctica,
how did those older girls know she had a million yen?
How did your mother know you were going to Antarctica before you told her?
Because I told them, of course!
I thought you would finally catch on and get mad at me...
But you and Antarctica and the others are such morons you did not catch on!
I do not know why I got so mad when you first told me
You always consulted with me before you did anything...
I know I have put you through a lot.
Yesterday, when you were talking, I finally realized.
You were not the one hanging on, I was.
Having you rely on me, consult with me... me getting exasperated with you,
pretending to mother you, acting so smart around you...
Because if I did not have that, I did not have anything.
Civilian Icebreaker Ship Leaves Port for First Time in Three Years
And because I was not anything, I did not want you to have anything.
You are not the one who was worthless.
I am the one who needs to go somewhere that is not here!
I am finally taking my first step
We are taking our first step.
To a world without any of the things we usually rely on.
To a world where we do not know what lies around the corner.
Where we do not even know which way home is.
To a world where we do not know where we will be tomorrow.
Where we cannot even imagine where we will be headed the next day.
Yet we are taking that step.
I have always loved watching it spill out all at once.
The energy stored up during its stagnation bursts forth.
